The paper deals with compressive sensing, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The proposed design of the measurement matrix is inspired by the construction of generalized low-density parity-check codes, which is a topic in coding theory (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the proposed scheme, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.MM) and theoretical computer science (cs.LG).
